ction: Chandan Das.				 																MUSIC				 																																	 August 14 at Charnock City, Salt Lake; 6.30 pm: Srabon Sandhya  an evening of Rabindrasangeet by Rakhi Sarkar and Sreyashi Mitra. Dr Rita Majumdar will render songs based on myriad moods.				 																																	 August 15 at Uttam Mancha; 6 pm: Pragna presents Tagore songs by Panchali Dhar, recitation from selected portions of Tagores work by Soumitra Chattopadhyay, and tunes of Rabindrasangeet on the piano, accordian, univox, key-board and melodika by V. Balsara.				 																																	 August 17 at Rotary Sadan; 6.30 pm: Quintessence presents Janani Aamaar  patriotic songs by Nupurchhanda Ghosh.				 																Art				 																																	 Till August 12 at Academy of Fine Arts, Central Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of paintings by Bimal Kar.				 																																	 Till August 13 at Chitrakoot Art Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: A Monsoon Melange  an exhibition of the works of various artists.				 																																	 August 13 (6 pm - 8 pm), August 14, 16 amp; 17 (4 pm - 8 pm) at Birla Academy of Art amp; Culture: Mongolian Mosaic  People amp; Design: A colourful set of 52 paintings (reproduction) depicting the unique costumes and head gear of different ethnic groups inhabiting the wild terrains of Mongolia.				 																																	 Till August 15 (except Monday) at Akar Prakar, P 238, Hindustan Park; 11 am - 8 pm: An exhibition of Susmit Biswas paintings.				 																																	 August 11 - 17 at Academy of Fine Arts, West gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of recent paintings by Sukanta Das begins from today.				 																																	 Till August 18 (except Tuesday) at Metropolitan Art Salon, 7 Chowringhee Road; 3 pm - 8 pm: An exhibition of the works of Arunesh Chowdhury, Mahadev Mukherjee, Subhendu Sarkar, Subrata Biswas and Sanjoy Sengupta.				 																								