092.				 																EXHIBITION				 																																	 Till August 13 at Crafts Council of West Bengal, 13 Chowringhee Terrace, 1st floor; 10 am - 7 pm, Monday (2 pm - 7 pm): A display of tribal rugs and accessories in Artisana, the new craft centre of Crafts Council of West Bengal.				 																SPORT				 																																	 Till August 23 at Space Circle: The second Corporate Indoor Cricket Tournament at 7,000 sq. ft, air-conditioned Royal Stag Skydrome.				 																film show				 																																	August 16 at Naatghar, Bharatiyam Cultural Multiplex, IB 201, Salt Lake; 6.30 pm: EZCC hosts the screening of Chakra, a film on Chhau dance of Seraikela.				 																ALBUM LAUNCH				 																																	 August 11 at Planet M, 22 Camac Street; 6.30 pm: Bhavna Records amp; Cassettes launches its music album, Emon Diney (compilation of selected songs and poems of Tagore). Panchali Dhar lends her voice in the songs and Soumitra Chatterjee contributes to the recitation bit.				 																MAGIC SHOW				 																																	 Till August 31 at Mahajati Sadan; 6.30 pm; Sundays (3 pm amp; 6.30 pm): Magic show by K. Lal.				 																festival				 																																	 August 11 at National High School, Sarat Bose Road; 10 am - 11 am amp; at Khalsa High School, 73 Paddapukur Road; 4 pm - 6 pm: In order to mark the 2510th Jayanthi of Adi Sankaracharya and also the golden jubilee celebration of Peetarohana of Sri Jayendra Saraswati, the Sri Adi Sankara Jyoti Ratham, carrying the gold idol of Jagadguru Adi Sankaracharya, the incarnation of Lord Shiva and Adi Sankara Jyoti lit by Pujyasri Jayendra Saraswati Mahaswamigal has reached Calcutta, and is now at Ved Bhavan.The Ratham will reach scheduled places for viewing.				 																																	 August 12 at Sri Thyagaraja Hall, P-530, Raja Basanta Roy Road; 7.30 am: Aavani Avittam Rig and Yajur Vedam will be celebrated by Guru Sathyanarayan Sastrigal and Sankara Sastrigal.				 																REUNION				 																																	 August 12 at the science building of Bethune School; 12 noon: Bethune School Praktani Samiti organises its Purnarmilan Utsav.				 																PHOTOGRAPHS				 																																	 August 17, 19, 20 amp; 21 at Nehru Childrens Museum; 1 pm - 6 pm: An exhibition of photographs depicting the different stages of Pandit Jawaharlal Nehrus life. Inauguration on August 16 at 4.45 pm.
